    • Method Detail

      • parseSetToTree

        public static RPNNode parseSetToTree(aprove.DPFramework.BasicStructures.TRSTerm trsTerm)
                              throws UnsupportetArithmeticSymbolException
        The parseSetToTree-method takes a TRSTerm and parses it into a RPNTree of RPNNode's using the subclasses to represent the corresponding TRSTerm's.
        TRSTerm-subclass corresponding RPNNode-subclass
        TRSVariable RPNVariable
        TRSConstantTerm RPNConstant
        TRSCompoundTerm RPNFunctionSymbol
        The method can work straight forward for TRSVariable's and TRSConstantTerm's and recursively calls parseSetToTree(TRSTerm) for the nested terms of a TRSCompoundTerm to derive the child RPNNode's of a RPNFunctionSymbol. WARNING: The method only provides a binary tree and does not support any ArithmeticalSymbol's other than the five ArithmeticalSymbol's stated.
        Parameters:
        trsTerm - the term that should be parsed
        Returns:
        the root node of the tree derived from the trsTerm
        Throws:
        UnsupportetArithmeticSymbolException - throws a UnsupportetArithmeticSymbolException if any other than the stated ArithmeticSymbol's occurs.
